Silicon Graphics Inc is raising 35 mlndlrs via an offering of convertible subordinated debentures due2012 with a 5-3/4 pct coupon and par pricing, said lead managerMorgan Stanley and Co Inc.    The debentures are convertible into the company's commonstock at 30.35 dlrs per share, representing a premium of 25.15pct over the stock price when terms on the debt were set.    Non-callable for two years, the issue is rated B-2 byMoody's Investors Service Inc and CCC-plus by Standard andPoor's Corp. Alex Brown and Sons Inc co-managed the deal. Reuter&#3;